Module it.polimi.ingsw.PSP034

Package it.polimi.ingsw.PSP034.view.CLI.printables

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    ANSI
    This class makes UNICODE escape characters available through functions and variables that have easy to understand names.
    Dialog
    This class creates a dialog to interact with the user.
    Drawing
    This class is used to generalize the type of different drawings.
    ErrorPrompt
    This class handles how the error messages are presented to the user.
    Font
    A Font object represents a string written with a special "font" created using the UNICODE box drawing characters.
    Frame
    This class creates and prints the frame of the CLI and also defines the dimension of the screen that will be used.
    LoserDrawing
    Represents the drawing that has to be displayed when the first player in a three player game loses.
    Message
    This class represents a message that can be printed in a Scene.
    OtherWinnerDrawing
    Represents the drawing that has to be displayed to the user when another player wins.
    PlayerBox
    Represents a card that contains information about a player.
    PrintableObject
    The PrintableObject class creates and handles objects that can be printed in a console.
    RegexCondition
    This class is used by the TextBox class to check that an input is valid.
    Spacer
    Represents an empty object used for spacing.
    TextBox
    This class is responsible for the interaction with the user.
    Title
    Represents the title of the game.
    ViewBoard
    Represents the game board.
    WinnerDrawing
    Represents the drawing that has to be displayed to the user he/she wins.
